Vendored reference code for the `pda_luxurywatch` benchmark.

  fsPDA_app.R    Shi & Huang's forward-selected PDA application script for the
                 China luxury-watch import study (forward selection by BIC, then
                 a prewhitened Newey-West post-selection t-test). Vendored
                 verbatim from the app1_luxury_watch/ folder of
                 github.com/zhentaoshi/fsPDA (file fsPDA.R).
  LICENSE.fsPDA  The fsPDA package's MIT license (Copyright (c) 2019 Zhentao Shi).

Source
  Shi, Zhentao & Jingyi Huang (2023), "Forward-Selected Panel Data Approach for
  Program Evaluation," Journal of Econometrics. Code: github.com/zhentaoshi/fsPDA
  (MIT). Vendored so the reference run is reproducible offline; all credit to the
  authors. reference.R reads basedata/china_watches_long.csv -- the same panel
  mlsynth fits -- pivots it to the script's expected form, and runs fsPDA().

Note: this is the authors' *application script*, which prewhitens the long-run
variance (the paper's Section 5 result). It differs from the packaged
est.fsPDA(), which does not prewhiten; mlsynth's PDA "fs" method ports the
application script. These files produce the captured reference bundle only and
are not part of the mlsynth library.
